<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Japirna Longtalon</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>1999-11-24 11:02:31</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>What more can I say, I'm level 30 and just got this weapon, and LOVE it.  I need to get my dex a little higher to get it to proc a little more, but other than that, i'm getting 1h slashes for 20 now using it, with only a 24 delay.  I've had it proc as little as once and as much as 4 times during a fight, so that's an extra 40 - 160 pts of damage just from the proc.  My dex is only 94 right now, so when i get it above 110, i'll see how much more it procs.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Tajom VanHackenSlash</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-11 11:46:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>WARNING:  The Ebony Blade is a really nice weapon that dishes out damage fast and has a cool proc.  This I am the first to agree with, but it has a major bad point.  I have seen it nicknamed as "Ranger's Bane" because once it Procs the mob CANNOT be snared, and if it has already been snared then it no longer is.  This WILL cause huge trains in most dungeon scenarios.  I recomend keeping your EB's as a trophy more than to actually use.</font></td></tr></table>
