<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kinoay-MithMarr</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-13 14:37:52</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Yes the blades have a bad point of breaking snare and the roots don't seem to last wrong, but a ranger can use them even in dungeon it just takes more effort and change of fighting style. I am currently duel wielding two EBSs with a Dex of 139 without spell buffs so I usually proc enough to keep my target in place but I have snare memed and in my hot box always ready to snare when the target is low and about to run. With little effort I have yet to lose control of a target in a dungeon.<BR>
Just a message to the rangers out there thinking about a EBS that they can work and with effort will reap great returns.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
