<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kanidil ap Dicter</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-27 17:06:20</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I have been using this great weapon for quite a few levels now (I'm level 39 at the moment)<BR>
and the blade has NEVER been the cause of a train yet. You do, however, have to be a <BR>
bit more careful. Most of the time the root doesn't hold and when it does it doesn't last<BR>
very long. So I just watch very carefully and snare as needed. At my level the blade procs<BR>
for 49 damage and I hit alot for 28 damage. (At level 50 the blade procs for 60 damage)<BR>
With a little care and caution this blade makes an excellent weapon and I have yet to get<BR>
in a group that tells me to ditch the weapon, although some people do ask me if it trains, heh.<BR>
<BR>
 - Kanidil ap Dicter  Level 39 Ranger on Rallos Zek</font></td></tr></table>
