<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I obtained 2 E Blades from a very good in game friend of mine recently.  I am very satisfied with the weapons.  I have not yet been told to leave a group or ditch the weapons.  But I have adapted my fighting style to enable me to time when I should resnare the mob.  I have noticed though that the people I group with get very impressed when i get 3 procs in a row and all of the sudden we are no longer wondering when to run but instead resting for the next pull.  I can understand though that some people not used to grouping with good rangers may be worried a bit, but if you know your group you should have no problem.  Just a few thoughts of mine. Oh I will never get rid of them either, think of the max output after the expansion.<BR>
